BM25-llava_documents.content: This statistic represents public perception of the role of the police in Great Britain in 2014. Preventing crime was, perhaps predictably, the most common answer. Keeping vulnerable people safe was only seen by 7 percent of respondents as being top priority.
BM25-llava_documents.title: Which of the following should be the most important part of the police's role?

BM25-llava_documents.content: According to a 2019/2020 survey, dogs are the most commonly owned pet in UK households. The share of households reporting dog ownership stands at 23 percent. The second most common house pet among UK households is a cat, with around 16 percent of respondents stating their ownership. In total, around 41 percent of UK households report owning at least one type of pet in 2019 and 2020. Pet ownership in the UK From 2011 to 2019, pet ownership in the UK has remained relatively constant. The share of pet ownership in UK households has hovered around 45-46 percent over the past nine years. However, the years 2016 and 2019 saw lower than average pet ownership, with just 40 percent of households saying they had a pet. The share of UK households owning a dog or cat over the past nine years has also remained relatively steady between 24 and 25 percent and between 17 and 18 percent respectively. Happiness, companionship and man’s best friend A 2019 survey asked dog owners to state their reasons for owning a dog and all linked their ownership to either improving their happiness and/or providing companionship. Happiness was the most common response, with 48 percent stating ‘because they make me happy... Whereas 45 percent stated their dogs provided ‘love/affection...and 35 percent stated their dogs provided ‘companionship... It seems the old saying "man’s best friend...still holds true to this day.
BM25-llava_documents.title: Leading pets ranked by household ownership in the United Kingdom (UK) in 2019/20

BM25-llava_documents.title: Do you think a strong fight against racism is necessary?

BM25_documents.title: Share of households owning a pet in the United Kingdom (UK) from 2009 to 2020

BM25_documents.content: With over 470 million dogs kept as pets worldwide, dogs came out on top as the leading type of pet in 2018. Within the same year, there were roughly 370 million pet cats in the world. Pets in the European Union While dogs were globally speaking the most common type of pet, cats were more common in the European Union in 2018. Roughly 75 million people within this region had a pet cat in 2018, compared to the 65 million pet dogs. That year, Germany had about nine and a half million pet dogs, making it the country with the highest number within the European Union. Other top dog-loving countries included the United Kingdom, Poland, and France. Other pets in Germany Besides cats and dogs, Germans had many other household pets in 2018. About five and a half million small pets, such as hamsters and rabbits, were kept by Germans that year. Additionally, about two million households in Germany owned an aquarium and roughly one and a half million households owned a garden pond.
BM25_documents.title: Number of dogs and cats kept as pets worldwide in 2018                                                     (in millions)

BM25_documents.content: And an overwhelming majority of those who view more assistance as necessary think Congress and the president should act on it as soon as possible, rather than waiting until after the presidential inauguration in January. About two-thirds of Americans (68%) say a new aid package is necessary and that it be acted upon by the president and current Congress.
BM25_documents.title: Most say new COVID-19 aid is needed – and want Congress to act ASAP

Clip_documents.content: The statistic shows the cat products purchased by consumers online in the last 12 months in the United States in 2018. During the survey, approximately 43 percent of cat owners reported buying dry pet food online in the preceding 12 months.
Clip_documents.title: Cat products purchased by consumers online in the last 12 months in the United States in 2018

Clip_documents.content: According to a 2018 survey which questioned dog owners who buy pet products online about their purchasing habits in the United States, 44 percent of respondents had bought dry dog food online in the past 12 months. Pet treats and chews were also a popular category to purchase through e-commerce channels. Why buy online rather than in-store? With the growth and development of e-commerce in the United States, more and more consumers are turning to online channels for all sorts of purchases. The number of U.S. households buying pet products online follows this trend ...in 2018 over 13,200 households bought such products online, almost 10,000 more than in 2013. According to a consumer survey, the leading motivations for shopping online for pet products include convenience, competitive pricing and increased value for money with the offer of free shipping. Leading dry dog food brands In 2017, Pedigree and Purina Dog Chow were the two leading named brands within the American dry dog food market, accounting for 10.9 and 9.4 percent of the total market respectively. This equated to sales of around 549.5 million U.S. dollars for Pedigree and 474.6 million U.S. dollars for Purina Dog Chow million U.S. dollars in that year.
Clip_documents.title: Dog products purchased by consumers online in the last 12 months in the United States in 2018

Qwen2_documents.content: In the United States, more than half of the population reported owning a pet in 2011. This number has been quite steady since then. Today there are more than 90 million cats in the United States, while the number of dogs is just below the 90 million-mark. Freshwater fish are the most common pet with almost 140 million nationwide in 2018, followed by the aforementioned cats and dogs. Pet expenses When it comes to expenses, fish are generally considered low maintenance compared to other pets. Dogs especially require high expense, particularly for kennel boarding while their owners are away. However, the highest costs for dog owners are due to surgical vet visits, reported at almost double the expense for cats in 2019. Lower life expectancy could be a factor - around 11 years for a medium-sized dog, compared with 12 to 15 years for cats. Pet food Food is currently the largest expense for cat owners, and the second highest for dogs, not even including treats. Despite the convenience of buying pet food online, or while already grocery shopping in a supermarket, food store, or wholesale club, the highest share of pet food sales comes from pet specialty chains. With many owners are willing to make the extra trip for their pets, chain shops Pet Smart and PetCo make up almost half the market for pet companies in the United States.
Qwen2_documents.title: Dog or cat ownership rates in households by race/ethnicity in the United States in 2011

Qwen2_documents.content: According to a national pet owners survey, there was a total of approximately 95.6 million cats living in households in the United States in 2017. In the same year, some 68 percent of all U.S. households owned at least one pet. Increasing pet expenditure Whilst the number of households owning cats, and pets in general, has remained relatively consistent over the last few years, pet industry expenditure has steadily grown. Consumers are expected to spend a record breaking 75.38 billion U.S. dollars on their pets in 2019. The majority of pet market revenue comes from food sales, followed by veterinary care costs. Shopping location preferences When it comes to shopping locations, most consumers still purchase their pet products in physical retail stores. However, the number of consumers buying pet products online is on the rise. Dry cat food was the number one pet product bought online by cat owners in the United States in 2018.
Qwen2_documents.title: Number of cats in the United States from 2000 to 2017                                                     (in millions)
